In this section, constraints related to the nutritional requirements to achieve the food security of population are described. Fruits, vegetables, grains, legumes and meat production (
                           f
                        ) are the different types of food involved to cover the food demand. Food production is determined by the availability of water and the land available for agriculture (mass balances are detailed in the supplementary material section). However, food production must be enough to cover the minimum recommended nutrients and calories (
                           n
                        ) that humans need to stay healthy (
                           Table 1

                        ). Therefore, the following constrains are included in the mathematical model to evaluate the optimal selection of technologies, as well as the agriculture and livestock outputs to achieve the WEF nexus security considering uncertain population, and water and energy demand.
